*Here’s a **full shake-down DotTalk++ script** that hits the big surfaces *(SCHEMAS/SELECT/USE/STRUCT/LIST/COUNT/TUP/LOCATE/CALC + all the new date/time functions, plus a **reversible** * * * CALCWRITE test on `GPA`).

Save as something like: `mcc_shakedown.dts`


* ------------------------------------------------------------
* MCC_SHAKEDOWN.DTS  (DotTalk++ / DotScript)
* Assumes your DBFs live under:  dbf\
* ------------------------------------------------------------

set echo on
echo ===== DotTalk++ MCC Shake-Down START =====

* ---- Clean slate / banner checks ----
color default
schemas close
schemas open dbf
schemas

echo ===== Basic command sanity =====
help
area

* ---- Quick per-table sanity: open/select/count/peek ----
echo ===== STUDENTS =====
select students
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

echo ===== TEACHERS =====
select teachers
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

echo ===== COURSES =====
select courses
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

echo ===== CLASSES =====
select classes
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

echo ===== ENROLL =====
select enroll
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

echo ===== DEPT =====
select dept
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

echo ===== BUILDING =====
select building
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

echo ===== ROOMS =====
select rooms
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

echo ===== TERMS =====
select terms
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

echo ===== MAJORS =====
select majors
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

echo ===== STUD_MAJ =====
select stud_maj
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

echo ===== TASSIGN =====
select tassign
area
struct
count
list 5
tup

* ---- Date/Time shake-down (run against STUDENTS for DOB/ENROLL_D) ----
echo ===== DATE/TIME FUNCTIONS (STUDENTS) =====
select students
list 1
tup

echo -- Clock calls (no DBF required, but we are open anyway)
calc date()
calc today()
calc time()
calc now()
calc datetime()

echo -- Field-driven date algebra
echo -- (DOB is a D field in STUDENTS)
calc dob
calc dob + 1
calc dob - 1
calc dateadd(dob, 30)
calc dateadd(dob, -30)

echo -- Date differences (days)
calc datediff(date(), dob)
calc date() - dob

echo -- Text -> Date (CTOD)
calc ctod(2000-01-01)
calc ctod("2000/01/01")
calc ctod(20000101)

echo -- Date + integer days
calc date() + 30
calc date() - 30

* ---- Boolean/predicate shake-down ----
echo ===== BOOLEAN / PREDICATE SHAKE-DOWN (STUDENTS) =====
select students
list 1
tup
calc gpa
calc gpa > 3
boolean gpa > 3
calc gpa >= 2 and gpa <= 4

* ---- String builtins shake-down via CALC TUPLE ----
echo ===== STRING BUILTINS (CALC TUPLE ...) =====
select students
list 1
tup
calc tuple upper(lname)
calc tuple lower(lname)
calc tuple proper(lname)
calc tuple left(lname, 3)
calc tuple right(fname, 2)
calc tuple alltrim(email)
calc tuple rtrim(lname)
calc tuple ltrim(fname)

* ---- LOCATE shake-down (case-insensitive feel) ----
echo ===== LOCATE SHAKE-DOWN =====
select students
locate for lname = davis
tup
locate for lname = taylor
tup

* ---- Reversible write test (exercises CALCWRITE record-lock path) ----
* NOTE: This changes GPA briefly, then restores it.
echo ===== REVERSIBLE WRITE TEST (GPA += .01 then -= .01) =====
select students
list 1
tup
calc gpa
calc gpa = gpa + 0.01
calc gpa
calc gpa = gpa - 0.01
calc gpa
tup

* ---- Color / UI sanity ----
echo ===== COLOR SANITY =====
color green
color amber
color default

echo ===== DotTalk++ MCC Shake-Down END =====
*quit

## Date/time function syntax rundown (what your new CALC supports)

All are **case-insensitive** in practice:

* **Clock calls**

  * `CALC DATE()` / `CALC TODAY()` → `YYYYMMDD`
  * `CALC TIME()` → `HHMMSS`
  * `CALC NOW()` / `CALC DATETIME()` → `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS`

* **Convert text to DBF date**

  * `CALC CTOD(2000-01-01)` → `20000101`
  * `CALC CTOD("2000/01/01")` → `20000101`
  * `CALC CTOD(20000101)` → `20000101`

* **Date arithmetic (days)**

  * `CALC <dateExpr> + <intDays>`

    * example: `CALC DOB + 1`
    * example: `CALC DATE() + 30`
  * `CALC <dateExpr> - <intDays>`

    * example: `CALC ENROLL_D - 7`

* **DATEADD**

  * `CALC DATEADD(<dateExpr>, <intDays>)`

    * example: `CALC DATEADD(DOB, 30)`
    * example: `CALC DATEADD(DATE(), -90)`

* **Date difference (days)**

  * `CALC <dateExprA> - <dateExprB>` → integer day count

    * example: `CALC DATE() - DOB`
  * `CALC DATEDIFF(<dateExprA>, <dateExprB>)` → integer day count

    * example: `CALC DATEDIFF(DATE(), DOB)`